<author><name><![CDATA[Gaurav]]></name></author>
<updated>2017-10-11T19:47:48-07:00</updated>
<published>2017-10-11T19:47:48-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7989&amp;p=34398#p34398</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7989&amp;p=34398#p34398"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Programs menu expands too quickly, no easy mouse escape]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7989&amp;p=34398#p34398"><![CDATA[
Go to General Behavior tab in Start menu Settings and uncheck the option &quot;All columns are same size&quot;. See if that makes the 4 columns of the submenu fit besides the main menu.<br /><br />Or you can hold down the Shift key before/while expanding the Programs item to expand it as a single column scrolling sub-menu.<br /><br />Those are about the only optimizations you can make right now.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Wed Oct 11, 2017 7:47 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
